cookieSettings.title = Cookie settings on HMRC services

cookieSettings.intro.paragraph1 = Cookies are files saved on your phone, tablet or computer when you visit a website
cookieSettings.intro.paragraph2 = We use cookies to store information about how you use HMRC services, such as the pages you visit.
cookieSettings.intro.paragraph3 = We use 4 types of cookie. You can choose which cookies you're happy for us to use.\
        
cookieSettings.usage.title = Cookies that measure website use
cookieSettings.usage.paragraph1 = We use Google Analytics to measure how you use the website so we can improve it based on user needs. We do not allow Google to use or share the data about how you use this site.
cookieSettings.usage.paragraph2 = Google Analytics sets cookies that store anonymised information about:
cookieSettings.usage.bullet1 = how you got to the site
cookieSettings.usage.bullet2 = the pages you visit on HMRC services and how long you spend on each page
cookieSettings.usage.bullet3 = what you click on while you're visiting the site
cookieSettings.usage.settinglabel.on = Use cookies that measure my website use
cookieSettings.usage.settinglabel.off = Do not use cookies that measure my website use
cookieSettings.usage.settingid = usage

cookieSettings.campaigns.title = Cookies that help with our communications and marketing
cookieSettings.campaigns.paragraph1 = These cookies may be set by third party websites and do things like measure how you view YouTube videos that are on HMRC services.
cookieSettings.campaigns.settinglabel.on = Use cookies that help with communications and marketing
cookieSettings.campaigns.settinglabel.off = Do not use cookies that help with communications and marketing
cookieSettings.campaigns.settingid = campaigns

cookieSettings.settings.title = Cookies that remember your settings
cookieSettings.settings.paragraph1 = These cookies do things like remember your preferences and the choices you make, to personalise your experience of using the site.
cookieSettings.settings.settinglabel.on = Use cookies that remember my settings on the site
cookieSettings.settings.settinglabel.off = Do not use cookies that remember my settings on the site
cookieSettings.settings.settingid = settings

cookieSettings.necessary.title = Strictly necessary cookies
cookieSettings.necessary.paragraph1 = These essential cookies do things like remember your progress through a form (for example a licence application)
cookieSettings.necessary.paragraph2 =They always need to be on.
cookieSettings.necessary.link.text = Find out more about cookies on HMRC services
cookieSettings.necessary.link.url = /help/cookies?abc=def&ghi=jkl


cookieSettings.onValue = on
cookieSettings.offValue = off
cookieSettings.saveButton = Save changes

service.name = Tracking Consent